race.comment: The weakest of maidens. FOR THE BRAVE (6) won't get a better chance to break through. Having first try at the mile and looks attractively weighted with the claim. Trained here and surprisingly first start at home but has the figures to break through this line-up. STRIKE ME PINK (5) placed at second outing here over 1300m then was disappointing on slow ground at Kilcoy. Better for the run and return home and to the mile. Senior rider goes aboard and worth another chance. VALLEY OF FAME (11) was at the tail last time on the Gold Coast but the run prior was close to the winner at Ipswich. Mixes form but best figures stack up and capable of sharp improvement. ROIGARD (10) turned in a better run latest but has had plenty of tries and despite the light weight prefer the place. CONCADOR (2) was poor fresh but strips fitter and extra trip should see some improvement.
